  "prompt": "How long can meth be detected through a urine drug screen?",
  "response": "Methamphetamine, commonly referred to as meth, can typically be detected in a urine drug screen for **1 to 4 days** after use. However, this detection window can vary depending on several factors, including:\n\n- **Frequency of use**: Chronic or heavy use can extend the detection period to **up to a week**.\n- **Metabolism**: Individual metabolic rates can influence how quickly meth is processed and eliminated from the body.\n- **Dose and potency**: Higher doses or more potent forms of meth may take longer to clear from the system.\n- **Urine pH and hydration**: Alkaline urine or dehydration can prolong the detection window.\n\nFor occasional users, meth is usually detectable in urine for **2 to 3 days**, while chronic users may test positive for **5 to 7 days** or even longer in some cases.",
